# Web Link Scanner (Python)

## 🛡️ Project Overview
This is a **simple Python-based Web Link Scanner** that crawls a website to extract all internal and external links.  
It is built using **only built-in Python modules**, so no external library installation is required.

The scanner is beginner-friendly and can be used for educational purposes to understand **web crawling and basic vulnerability scanning concepts**.


## 🧰 Technologies Used
- Python 3.x  
- Built-in modules:
  - `urllib.request` → for HTTP requests  
  - `urllib.parse` → to join and parse URLs  
  - `html.parser` → to parse HTML and extract links  
  - `socket` → to handle timeout  

No additional libraries are required.

## 📝 Features
- Crawls all links from a given website URL  
- Handles URL joining to make absolute URLs  
- Sets timeout to avoid long waiting on unresponsive sites  
- User-Agent header included to mimic a browser request  
- Prints the total number of links found  


## 💻 How to Use

1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/web-link-scanner.git
cd web-link-scanner

##Run the Python scanner:
1.python scanner.py
2.Enter the target website URL when prompted:
3.Enter URL: http://example.com

##Sample Output
Enter URL: http://example.com

[+] Getting links...
[+] Found 5 links

[✔] Scan Complete
[+] Found 5 links → indicates the number of links extracted from the website.
[✔] Scan Complete → indicates that crawling is finished successfully.

##How It Works
Crawling Links

The LinkParser class inherits from HTMLParser and extracts all <a> tag href attributes.
Handling URLs

Extracted relative URLs are converted to absolute URLs using urljoin.
Opening URLs

urlopen is used with a User-Agent header to mimic browser requests.
Timeout is set via socket.setdefaulttimeout(10) to avoid hanging on unresponsive URLs.
Output

Prints the total number of links found.
Designed as a foundation to add further features like XSS/SQL scanning in future.

##🔮 Future Improvements
Add XSS and SQL injection detection
Multi-threaded crawling for speed
Export results to a CSV or PDF report
Build a GUI version for easier use

